24/07/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Romanian wheat producers' association announced Friday (22 July) that bread prices were expected to rise by 10 per cent, due to the heavy floods that damaged after this year's wheat crops.
According to the association, the hike will take place in the next two months.
The Agriculture Ministry has estimated the losses caused by the floods at 130m euros.
(Rompres - 22/07/05)
